author: @ABSSBABSA
text: from tensorflow.keras.layers import Input, Lambda, Dense, Flatten from tensorflow.keras.models import Model from tensorflow.keras.applications.inception_v3 import InceptionV3 from tensorflow.keras.applications.inception_v3 import preprocess_input from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing import image from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator, load_img from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential import numpy as np from glob import glob 		 #resize all images to this IMAGE_SIZE = [224,224]  # Verify and correct paths if needed train_path = 'content/drive/My Drive/PlantDiseaseDatasetAug/train' valid_path = 'content/drive/My Drive/PlantDiseaseDatasetAug/valid'  # Print paths for verification print("Train Path:", train_path) print("Valid Path:", valid_path)   inception = InceptionV3(input_shape=IMAGE_SIZE + [3] , weights='imagenet', include_top=False)  for layer in inception.layers:       layer.trainable=False 	   # Print list of folders inside the 'train' directory folders = glob(train_path + '/*') print("Folders inside 'train' directory:", folders)   # our layers - you can add more if you want x = Flatten()(inception.output)  prediction = Dense(len(folders), activation = 'softmax')(x)  # create a model object model = Model(inputs=inception.input, outputs=prediction)  #view the structure of the model model.summary()   # tell the model which cost and optimization methods to used model.compile(  loss='categorical_crossentropy',  optimizer='adam',  metrics=['accuracy'] )  # use the image data generator to import the images from the dataset  from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator  train_datagen = ImageDataGenerator( rescale= 1./255, 								    shear_range=0.2, 									zoom_range=0.2, 									horizontal_flip=True) test_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1./255)   #Make sure you provide the same target size as initialized for the image size training_set = train_datagen.flow_from_directory('content/drive/My Drive/PlantDiseaseDatasetAug/train', 												target_size=(224,224), 												batch_size=32, 												class_mode='categorical')   # fit the model # run the cell. it will take some time to execute  # Use model.fit for training r = model.fit(     training_set,     validation_data=test_set,     epochs=10,     steps_per_epoch=len(training_set),     validation_steps=len(test_set) )    import matplotlib.pyplot as plt  #plot the loss plt.plot(loss_values) plt.show()
